text: Tora Øyna (31 March 1898 – 5 February 1991) was a Norwegian politician for the Centre Party. She served as a deputy representative to the Norwegian Parliament from Vest-Agder during the terms 1958-1961 and 1961-1965\. ==References== * Category:1898 births Category:1991 deaths Category:Centre Party (Norway) politicians Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Vest-Agder politicians Category:Women members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian women politicians Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
